                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "To circumvent these issues, we propose to use the secant bundle, which was introduced by R.L.E. Schwarzenberger in [11] for the purpose of giving fiber bundle structure of secant lines. While the original construction was based on symmetric product of a given variety, rather than the Hilbert scheme of points, in this paper we adopt the convention presented in [3] and [15] where the secant bundle is a projective bundle over a Hilbert scheme of points. This approach has been used in previous works such as [3], [13], [14] and [15], where the secant bundles was used as a tool for describing the singularity and the normality of the 2- secant variety. In this paper, we utilize the birational morphism from the secant bundle to the 2- secant variety as a resolution of singularities."
                                }
